<%#
  # Partial: _radio-group.html
  # Date: 11/23/2025
  # Author: MoisÃ©s Reis
  # Package: Meta
  #
  # Description: Defines the structural wrapper for a group of card-style radio button options.
  #              It provides a title, descriptive text, and horizontal list container for the choices.
  #
  # Usage: - What: Renders the outer container for a set of mutually exclusive radio button cards.
  #                Ensures consistent styling and context for the radio choices.
  #        - How: Requires `title` (string) and `desc` (string) local variables to provide context.
  #               The individual radio options (rendered via `_card_radio.html`) must be passed into the block using `yield`.
  #        - Why: Centralizes the shared elements (title, description, and list structure)
  #               that belong to a single radio button group, promoting reusability and clean form design.
  %>
<div class="flex flex-col justify-start gap-3">
  <div class="flex flex-col justify-start gap-1.5">
    <%= content_tag :h3, title, class: "text-2xs font-heading uppercase leading-none font-semibold" %>
    <%= content_tag :p, desc, class: "text-xs text-muted leading-none font-normal" %>
  </div>
  <ul class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
    <%= yield %>
  </ul>
</div>